Influence of cigarette-smoking on the result of the triple test. The aim was to establish whether the risk of trisomy 21 in women smokers undergoing triple test differs to women nonsmokers, whether increased smoking changes the hormonal values, and if the cessation of smoking at the beginning of pregnancy has any influence on the triple test. 1,854 pregnant women were interviewed regarding their smoking habits at the time of the triple test. They were divided into 5 groups: (a) nonsmokers (b) smokers before pregnancy